<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,978,1284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
I (
<bibRefCitation author="Westcott" box="[176,348,978,1004]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="Westcott, R. L. (2005) Two new species of Acmaeodera Eschscholtz and two new species of Mastogenius Solier (Coleoptera: Buprestidae) from Mexico. Folia Entomologica Mexicana, 44 (Supl. 1), 35 - 43." type="journal article" year="2005">
Westcott 
<number box="[288,348,978,1004]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) stated that the specific epithet for this species is a noun in apposition. However, according to Article 
<number box="[274,332,1018,1044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="11.9">11.9</number>
. 
<number box="[336,346,1018,1044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1.0">1</number>
of the 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[434,593,1018,1044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, 306 p." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode box="[434,503,1018,1044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">ICZN</collectionCode>
(
<number box="[521,584,1018,1044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, a noun in apposition must be singular; therefore, the original name is unavailable and creation of a new species is necessary. This new species follows my (
<number box="[1184,1246,1058,1084]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="2005.0">2005</number>
) description for 
<taxonomicName box="[151,317,1099,1124]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Mastogenius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyanelytra">
<emphasis box="[151,317,1099,1124]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">M. cyanelytra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[402,504,1098,1124]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">holotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[560,740,1099,1124]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Mastogenius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyanelytron">
<emphasis box="[560,740,1099,1124]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">M. cyanelytron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is as designated in that publication for the former name: “ 
<collectingCountry box="[161,283,1138,1164]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">MEXICO</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[296,389,1138,1164]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">México</collectingCountry>
, 
<quantity box="[402,495,1138,1164]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="m" value="2800.0">2800 m</quantity>
, Santa Catarina del Monte, 
<quantity box="[828,903,1138,1164]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="km" value="12.0">12 km</quantity>
(air) ESE Texcoco, 
<date box="[1148,1284,1138,1164]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1999-07-23">
<number box="[1148,1179,1138,1164]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="23.0">23</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[1221,1284,1138,1164]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</date>
, R. L. Westcott, beating 
<taxonomicName box="[306,494,1179,1204]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis box="[306,494,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Quercus rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<typeStatus box="[503,657,1178,1204]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="R. L. Westcott" authorityName="R. L. Westcott" box="[666,1132,1178,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Mastogenius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyanelytra">
<emphasis box="[666,948,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Mastogenius cyanelytra</emphasis>
R. L. Westcott
</taxonomicName>
, deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[1297,1391,1178,1204]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/10ei-x9nj" name="Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">UNAM</collectionCode>
. In my opinion the 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[338,492,1218,1244]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, 306 p." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode box="[338,407,1218,1244]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">ICZN</collectionCode>
(
<number box="[423,484,1218,1244]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
needs clarification regarding how to rectify unavailable names as therein I cannot find any specific mention of that process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1378,1444]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">The following three species are discussed in detail, and because of their close and complex relationship are presented together for ease of comparison.</paragraph>
